<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-18807] Group coordinator under-reports thread idle time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18807</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When events arrive at the event processor with less than group.coordinator.threads ms between them, the thread idle time is rounded down to 0 because of integer division.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;eg. when the group coordinator has 8 threads, and it receives &amp;gt;1k offset commit requests per second evenly split across shards, the thread idle time metric will be under-reported.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/2353a7c5081b53402d5092afd255e2bdf7aa2d20/coordinator-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/common/runtime/MultiThreadedEventProcessor.java#L141&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/2353a7c5081b53402d5092afd255e2bdf7aa2d20/coordinator-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/common/runtime/MultiThreadedEventProcessor.java#L141&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
